<font color="#FF0000">IT WAS A NICE DAY.</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov 12  2:50:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Gary,<br><br>
Welcome here!  Good to hear from you.<br><br>
I spent the day, first at a work appointment, then at the Veteran's Day parade here in little Roseburg, Oregon.  We had three high school bands in the parade, including our local Roseburg High School Band with my boy, Nathan, in it.  'Got a few pictures of him marching too.  I wore my Beret and gave some salutes to the WWII and Korean War Vets in the floats from the VA Hospital here.  'Got some snappy salutes back too.  We had everything from cub scouts to high school marching bands to farm tractors (from the 1930's).  It was very enjoyable.<br><br>
This year I did not feel low like I have in years past, and I'm sure that this dialog we've had here had something to do with it.  Thanks to all!<br><br>
I also had something really neat happen too.  Yesterday I received a virtual boquet of red roses from the woman who was the daughter of my flying buddy, Jim Thomas.  I only found out in the last year that Jim was killed in November 1971 while participating on a rescue mission.  That made this holiday for me.  
